1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:07,074

2
00:00:31,011 --> 00:00:33,202
Quiet on the set. And we're rolling.

3
00:00:33,180 --> 00:00:34,938
Cody Maverick interview, take one.

4
00:00:35,315 --> 00:00:36,782
Why are you guys here
to interview me?

5
00:00:36,950 --> 00:00:39,077
It's what we do.
We're a reality film crew.

6
00:00:39,653 --> 00:00:41,814
Should I know some of the questions
before we start?

7
00:00:41,989 --> 00:00:44,457
- No. They're easy.
- Okay.

8
00:00:44,625 --> 00:00:47,185
- Can you stand on that box, please?
- Oh, yeah.

9
00:00:48,795 --> 00:00:51,263
Right there? What is that?

10
00:00:51,465 --> 00:00:53,433
- What is that?
- A sound thing. It's a microphone.

11
00:00:53,600 --> 00:00:54,862
What's up, man? I'm Cody.

12
00:00:55,035 --> 00:00:56,798
And you're what, 14, 15 years old?

13
00:00:57,070 --> 00:00:59,004
Seventeen years of age.

14
00:00:59,172 --> 00:01:01,163
And any other skills
besides surfing?

15
00:01:01,375 --> 00:01:03,309
Like what?
Like singing and dancing?

16
00:01:03,477 --> 00:01:04,466
Yeah. Yeah.

17
00:01:06,480 --> 00:01:08,175
No, not me, man. I just surf.

18
00:01:08,348 --> 00:01:09,838
- Loser.
- I just...

19
00:01:11,084 --> 00:01:12,483
Cut it out, Glen. Stop, man.

20
00:01:12,552 --> 00:01:14,142
We're here to make
a movie about Cody.

21
00:01:14,321 --> 00:01:16,050
- Does he have to be here?
- It's gonna be great.

22
00:01:16,156 --> 00:01:18,050
Can I get in line now to not see it?

23
00:01:18,058 --> 00:01:18,600
We'll re-slate.

24
00:01:19,493 --> 00:01:22,360
Since we're talking about surfing,
give us your thoughts about surfing.

25
00:01:22,562 --> 00:01:23,893
Surfing. Surfing.

26
00:01:25,399 --> 00:01:28,300
- Where do I start?
- How about at the beginning?

27
00:01:28,535 --> 00:01:30,400
Okay, well...

28
00:01:31,104 --> 00:01:36,167
So as soon as there was the first wave,
right? There was the first surfer.

29
00:01:37,711 --> 00:01:41,738
All they needed was, like,
a piece of driftwood...

30
00:01:41,915 --> 00:01:45,510
...a block of ice or something like
that, and then they were off.

31
00:01:46,420 --> 00:01:49,355
And they were hooked, man.
They were hooked.

32
00:01:52,592 --> 00:01:56,824
Up till recent times, you had
your old dudes. Your hang-six cats.

33
00:01:56,997 --> 00:01:59,966
These old guys used to lay down
with these huge, humongous boards.

34
00:02:00,467 --> 00:02:03,436
These guys were the pioneers...

35
00:02:03,637 --> 00:02:06,697
...but nobody saw
what surfing could really be...

36
00:02:07,274 --> 00:02:09,504
...until Big Z did it.

37
00:02:09,676 --> 00:02:12,770
- Could you tell us who Big Z was?
- Who was Big Z?

38
00:02:12,946 --> 00:02:17,610
You're asking the right guy.
You got that far. Z is everything.

39
00:02:17,818 --> 00:02:19,513
Big Z is surfing.
I mean, he's...

40
00:02:19,686 --> 00:02:21,847
There may well as not have been
an ocean before Z.

41
00:02:22,022 --> 00:02:24,149
They invented the ocean for him.

42
00:02:26,226 --> 00:02:29,627
He lived so hard
because he wasn't afraid to live.

43
00:02:29,996 --> 00:02:31,861
He wasn't afraid to die.

44
00:02:43,310 --> 00:02:46,074
He came to Antarctica
when I was just a kid.

45
00:02:47,647 --> 00:02:50,775
Man, it was the biggest thing
that ever happened here.

46
00:02:52,486 --> 00:02:54,681
And suddenly there he was.

47
00:02:54,855 --> 00:03:00,316
Just floating over the water.
Hovering, you know, like weightless.

48
00:03:04,264 --> 00:03:06,732
He could've walked up to anyone...

49
00:03:07,601 --> 00:03:10,399
...and he walks right up to me.

50
00:03:11,771 --> 00:03:15,366
And he gives me this awesome,
one-of-a-kind Big Z necklace.

51
00:03:16,309 --> 00:03:20,040
And then he tells me,
"You know, kid, never give up.

52
00:03:20,213 --> 00:03:23,705
Find a way,
because that's what winners do. "

53
00:03:26,887 --> 00:03:29,117
He was the greatest.

54
00:03:30,323 --> 00:03:33,690
Everyone looked up to him,
respected him, loved him.

55
00:03:35,950 --> 00:03:37,900
And one day, one day
I'm gonna be just like him.

56
00:03:51,556 --> 00:03:53,450
And I've been surfing
ever since I can remember.

57
00:03:55,075 --> 00:03:57,700
It's hard to imagine my life
when I wasn't surfing.

58
00:03:58,165 --> 00:04:01,300
I want to get out of here,
and this is my ticket out.

59
00:04:01,700 --> 00:04:04,650
I'm really good, man.
I'm the best on the island.

60
00:04:05,050 --> 00:04:10,900
I know it sounds cocky for saying that,
but, I mean, I am, like the best.

61
00:04:17,936 --> 00:04:20,700
I was born and raised here
in Shiverpool.

62
00:04:22,674 --> 00:04:24,437
Lived here my whole life.

63
00:04:25,010 --> 00:04:28,639
That's where they sort the fish. It's
the dumbest thing I've ever heard of.

64
00:04:28,813 --> 00:04:33,682
But yeah, I worked there
just to pacify my mom a little bit.

65
00:04:34,419 --> 00:04:36,580
Good old Shiverpool.

66
00:04:37,923 --> 00:04:39,356
This place sucks, bro.

67
00:04:39,991 --> 00:04:44,087
I worked my way up from the sardine
pile, then to the mackerel pile...

68
00:04:44,262 --> 00:04:46,093
...and I ended up
on the gefilte fish pile.

69
00:04:46,264 --> 00:04:48,562
- All hard work.
- Not like some I could mention.

70
00:04:48,733 --> 00:04:50,928
Yes, this farkakte kid
with the thing on the water.

71
00:04:51,436 --> 00:04:52,494
My house?

72
00:04:52,671 --> 00:04:54,764
Over there. You see it
right there with the surfboards?

73
00:04:55,674 --> 00:04:59,041
Yeah, I just live here with me
and my brother, Glen, my mom.

74
00:05:00,145 --> 00:05:02,375
He was a little, teeny, small egg.

75
00:05:03,848 --> 00:05:05,281
He wasn't very impressive.

76
00:05:05,450 --> 00:05:07,441
Glen was the big egg,
Cody was the small egg.

77
00:05:08,186 --> 00:05:10,620
He can't help it.
That's just the way he is.

78
00:05:10,789 --> 00:05:11,881
I mean, he's out there...

79
00:05:13,224 --> 00:05:16,682
...in the water all day
shirking his responsibilities.

80
00:05:17,062 --> 00:05:20,520
You know, hatching these eggs
is a big responsibility.

81
00:05:20,732 --> 00:05:22,996
And my brother, Cody,
he just doesn't understand that.

82
00:05:23,201 --> 00:05:27,797
- He needs to step up and be a man.
- It takes a real man to sit on an egg.

83
00:05:27,973 --> 00:05:30,942
- You know it.
- Quincy, come to Daddy.

84
00:05:31,109 --> 00:05:33,270
He wants to be different.
All the time with the different.

85
00:05:33,445 --> 00:05:34,810
Who's got the time in the day to...

86
00:05:34,980 --> 00:05:36,470
Only six months in a day.

87
00:05:36,648 --> 00:05:38,445
- Thanks for making it.
- Sorry. It was too good to miss.

88
00:05:38,617 --> 00:05:41,085
- Thanks for making it.
- How was it out there?

89
00:05:41,252 --> 00:05:42,981
He's the big brother.
I'm the little brother.

90
00:05:43,388 --> 00:05:44,980
I'm not touching you.

91
00:05:45,156 --> 00:05:46,646
- Not gonna touch you.
- Do you see this?

92
00:05:46,825 --> 00:05:48,087
- Don't. Please?
- I'm not.

93
00:05:48,259 --> 00:05:49,624
He makes sure that I know that.

94
00:05:50,061 --> 00:05:53,553
I had to fight for everything.
Even Mom's tuna casserole.

95
00:06:00,772 --> 00:06:01,864
I'm lucky I survived.

96
00:06:02,040 --> 00:06:05,066
It really wasn't that easy
for him growing up.

97
00:06:05,677 --> 00:06:07,304
Like I said before...

98
00:06:08,380 --> 00:06:10,575
...he never really knew his father.

99
00:06:13,485 --> 00:06:17,649
I'm not really the person to ask about it
because I was too young to remember.

100
00:06:17,822 --> 00:06:20,416
Look, I'm not the only kid
on the island...

101
00:06:20,592 --> 00:06:24,119
...whose dad was, you know, eaten.

102
00:06:24,829 --> 00:06:30,096
- Still, it had to be traumatic.
- No. Not for me, bro. Not for me.

103
00:06:31,536 --> 00:06:34,699
- What's your dream?
- To go away.

104
00:06:35,440 --> 00:06:38,876
- To go away. That's great.
- Do you guys want a drink?

105
00:06:39,044 --> 00:06:42,104
Got to run away
from responsibility and life.

106
00:06:42,280 --> 00:06:43,542
This is unique.

107
00:06:43,715 --> 00:06:45,910
- This is not the norm.
- "I have dreams."

108
00:06:47,285 --> 00:06:50,118
- When is this not happening?
- Don't make that noise.

109
00:06:52,190 --> 00:06:54,283
- Cody!
- It's really disrespectful.

110
00:06:55,326 --> 00:06:56,657
I would never do that.

111
00:06:58,730 --> 00:07:00,459
You just wouldn't make it
out of your mouth.

112
00:07:00,632 --> 00:07:02,293
That's the difference
between you and me.

113
00:07:02,500 --> 00:07:04,730
You know what?
I can't do this anymore.

114
00:07:04,903 --> 00:07:06,131
Mom. Look what you did.

115
00:07:06,304 --> 00:07:08,670
This is for me. This isn't for you.
Why is Glen still here?

116
00:07:08,840 --> 00:07:11,365
Oh, yeah, exactly. Mom!

117
00:07:11,543 --> 00:07:13,477
I don't understand why
everybody's so judgmental.

118
00:07:13,645 --> 00:07:15,840
I understand why Mom's judgmental.

119
00:07:16,014 --> 00:07:19,575
I think it's because she cares,
partially. It's also partially because...

120
00:07:19,751 --> 00:07:22,242
...everyone else is looking at her like,
"Hey, Cody's just a bum.

121
00:07:22,420 --> 00:07:24,820
Cody's this. Cody's that.
Cody's this. "

122
00:07:25,490 --> 00:07:28,050
Cody's me, bro. Let me be me.

123
00:07:28,693 --> 00:07:30,388
When is that gonna start?

124
00:07:42,907 --> 00:07:45,740
You know what they call me?
The dream maker. The dream maker.

125
00:07:47,145 --> 00:07:49,113
I find these kids,
I bring them here...

126
00:07:49,280 --> 00:07:52,511
...and I give them a chance
to be somebody.

127
00:07:53,618 --> 00:07:56,485
You know my greatest joy
as a surf promoter? Finding Z.

128
00:07:56,654 --> 00:07:58,121
Watching him rise to the top.

129
00:07:58,289 --> 00:08:02,521
I still can't believe he's gone.
He was like a son to me, you know?

130
00:08:02,694 --> 00:08:06,460
It was a heart thing, you know?
Can we just take five minutes?

131
00:08:06,698 --> 00:08:09,792
How's my hair? Is it messed up?
I ain't got all day. Is it mussed?

132
00:08:09,968 --> 00:08:11,663
We just have a few more questions
about Big Z.

133
00:08:11,836 --> 00:08:13,531
But right now
I think we're more interested...

134
00:08:13,705 --> 00:08:16,071
...in the Reggie Belafonte story,
and who could blame us?

135
00:08:16,241 --> 00:08:17,970
But Big Z is kind of the focus
of our...

136
00:08:18,143 --> 00:08:20,043
Let's get the coconut filler guy
over here.

137
00:08:20,211 --> 00:08:21,838
And how about the guy
sweeping the sand?

138
00:08:22,013 --> 00:08:25,813
Can we hear your boring story
about your tedious, ridiculous life?

139
00:08:25,984 --> 00:08:27,679
Get your feathers off it! Stop!

140
00:08:27,886 --> 00:08:29,820
I ain't got all day.
I got a big production here.

141
00:08:29,988 --> 00:08:31,148
Roll, okay? Just roll!

142
00:08:31,556 --> 00:08:35,549
Welcome, fans, to another edition
of SPEN Sports.

143
00:08:35,994 --> 00:08:37,359
This is Sal Masakela...

144
00:08:37,529 --> 00:08:41,863
...and we're here at the surfing capital
of the world, Pen Gu Island...

145
00:08:42,033 --> 00:08:46,333
...for a preview of the tenth annual
Big Z Memorial Surf-Off.

146
00:08:47,338 --> 00:08:49,397
Professional surfers
extraordinaire...

147
00:08:49,574 --> 00:08:51,439
...Kelly and Rob tell us...

148
00:08:51,609 --> 00:08:54,009
...what challenges
our surfers are going to face.

149
00:08:55,413 --> 00:08:57,938
First things first, Sal. The wave.
It's the perfect combination...

150
00:08:58,116 --> 00:09:02,576
...of beauty and danger. Even
the pros are terrified of this place.

151
00:09:04,622 --> 00:09:05,782
Hi, Mom.

152
00:09:05,957 --> 00:09:07,481
Dig this, Sal. Section behind me.

153
00:09:08,827 --> 00:09:11,125
It's "The Boneyards."
Few surfers have ventured in there...

154
00:09:11,296 --> 00:09:12,320
...and come out alive.

155
00:09:12,497 --> 00:09:15,091
Are you trying to tell me
people have died here?

156
00:09:15,266 --> 00:09:17,894
- That's right, Sal.
- A moment of silence for them.

157
00:09:18,069 --> 00:09:22,130
And we keep it moving because
if the Boneyards was not enough...

158
00:09:22,307 --> 00:09:26,209
...our surfers will be facing off with
Tank "The Shredder" Evans.

159
00:09:26,377 --> 00:09:29,210
Tank, nine-time defending champ.

160
00:09:30,014 --> 00:09:31,311
A role model? No.

161
00:09:32,817 --> 00:09:35,445
But I do consider myself somebody
that everyone should look up to.

162
00:09:35,620 --> 00:09:38,214
Kids should try to pretend
that they're Tank.

163
00:09:38,389 --> 00:09:40,857
I mean, they should try.
Good luck, kids.

164
00:09:41,793 --> 00:09:44,353
You never want to get in there
and help them out...

165
00:09:44,529 --> 00:09:48,260
...and show them how to surf
and spend some time with the kids?

166
00:09:48,433 --> 00:09:50,094
No, I don't want to do that.

167
00:09:50,268 --> 00:09:52,498
- Anyway, this is my wave.
- Always classy Tank Evans.

168
00:09:52,670 --> 00:09:55,400
Coming up after the break,
penguin dodge ball. Stick around.

169
00:09:56,841 --> 00:10:00,174
Okay, to get back to the competition,
I just want to say:

170
00:10:00,345 --> 00:10:03,280
I'm scouring the globe
for the next big thing.

171
00:10:03,615 --> 00:10:04,980
But that's another story.

172
00:10:09,520 --> 00:10:11,147
He doesn't look for them.
I find them.

173
00:10:12,523 --> 00:10:14,047
I find these penguins.
I find the talent.

174
00:10:15,393 --> 00:10:16,985
Reggie has sent me everywhere
on this trip.

175
00:10:17,228 --> 00:10:18,718
Anyplace there's an ocean...

176
00:10:20,064 --> 00:10:21,691
...a lake, a puddle.
It's ridiculous.

177
00:10:23,034 --> 00:10:25,832
I am on so much migraine medication,
you have no idea.

178
00:10:26,004 --> 00:10:29,167
The stress is killing me. I don't know
how much longer I can last.

179
00:10:29,340 --> 00:10:31,331
I have to tell you that right now.

180
00:10:34,245 --> 00:10:36,406
You gotta try
this blowhole thing, man.

181
00:10:36,581 --> 00:10:38,845
This whale dude
is giving me a brain freeze.

182
00:10:41,519 --> 00:10:42,986
I lost a bet.

183
00:10:43,388 --> 00:10:45,720
Excuse me. Excuse me.

184
00:10:45,890 --> 00:10:49,348
Does anybody
in this entire frozen wasteland surf?

185
00:10:49,527 --> 00:10:52,155
- The Cody Maverick kid does that.
- Wonderful. Thank you.

186
00:10:52,363 --> 00:10:54,331
You know, you're sitting on...
thin ice.

187
00:10:54,499 --> 00:10:57,627
Excuse me, I'm looking for...
I'm looking for Cody Maverick.

188
00:10:57,802 --> 00:11:01,431
- Has anyone seen Cody Maverick?
- I'm Cody Maverick.

189
00:11:02,874 --> 00:11:06,037
Mike Abromowitz from the Big Z
Memorial Surf-Off, Pen Gu Island.

190
00:11:06,210 --> 00:11:08,041
You came here on a wha...
You came to see me. Wow!

191
00:11:08,212 --> 00:11:12,308
- Quite a slip-and-slider, aren't you?
- You're here. What an honor, sir.

192
00:11:12,483 --> 00:11:14,849
Lovely. Wonderful. I hear you surf.

193
00:11:15,019 --> 00:11:16,611
- Is this true?
- You gotta see what I can do.

194
00:11:16,788 --> 00:11:18,483
- You can actually stand on a board?
- I'll be back.

195
00:11:18,656 --> 00:11:20,851
You're gonna see what I can do
everything's gonna be good...

196
00:11:21,025 --> 00:11:23,516
...and I'm coming with you.
- I can't imagine a better day.

197
00:11:23,695 --> 00:11:27,722
Ma! Ma, he came... the scout.
Mikey. He came. He's here.

198
00:11:27,899 --> 00:11:30,561
- What? Yeah.
- He's giving me a shot now, Ma.

199
00:11:30,735 --> 00:11:32,293
You want to come watch me surf?

200
00:11:32,470 --> 00:11:34,404
- No, that's okay.
- Just this time.

201
00:11:34,572 --> 00:11:39,373
- I'm busy. I'm chopping here.
- Okay. All right, well, wish me luck.

202
00:11:39,544 --> 00:11:42,843
Cody, just be careful
of those big waves.

203
00:11:45,750 --> 00:11:47,809
Well, anytime now.

204
00:11:48,152 --> 00:11:52,282
You should have been here yesterday.
We had a sweet swell yesterday.

205
00:11:52,457 --> 00:11:55,426
I was doing some layback 360s
and floaters. It was insane.

206
00:11:55,593 --> 00:11:56,924
Wow! Start the whale.

207
00:11:57,095 --> 00:11:59,029
No! Wait! Wait!
Just give me one more chance.

208
00:11:59,197 --> 00:12:00,858
- All I need is one, please.
- You just had it.

209
00:12:01,032 --> 00:12:02,966
- Dude, please don't go.
- Tough break, kid.

210
00:12:03,134 --> 00:12:05,500
- Just wait one second.
- Better luck next year. Move it.

211
00:12:05,670 --> 00:12:08,605
- Let's go. He's coming!
- Just one wave. That's all I need.

212
00:12:09,207 --> 00:12:12,699
I've never won anything
my whole life.

213
00:12:14,045 --> 00:12:16,479
Just once I want to feel like a winner.

214
00:12:16,948 --> 00:12:21,044
I used to scout songbirds. Toucans
for this musical revue in Brazil.

215
00:12:21,219 --> 00:12:23,483
Now that's show business.
Toucans...

216
00:12:23,654 --> 00:12:24,712
Hold on!

217
00:12:25,723 --> 00:12:28,487
I don't care what you say,
I'm coming to Pen Gu!

218
00:12:28,659 --> 00:12:33,494
No way, no how.
This is a contest for big-wave surfers.

219
00:12:33,664 --> 00:12:36,155
Can't this blubber ball go any faster?
Step on it, fish sticks!

220
00:12:38,069 --> 00:12:40,128
No, no, no, no!

221
00:12:45,076 --> 00:12:48,170
Poor kid. I feel bad a little bit.
Honestly, this is embar...

222
00:12:48,346 --> 00:12:49,813
No, wait! Wait!

223
00:13:01,626 --> 00:13:03,457
Did you guys see that?
He almost had my board!

224
00:13:04,429 --> 00:13:07,262
He almost had it.
Next time we'll get it.

225
00:13:07,432 --> 00:13:09,297
- Yeah, so anyway...
- Wait!

226
00:13:30,788 --> 00:13:34,053
We got you. We got you.
Oh, you are heavier than you look.

227
00:13:35,026 --> 00:13:36,288
- Man, we did it.
- Thank you.

228
00:13:36,461 --> 00:13:37,951
Teamwork always pays off.

229
00:13:38,129 --> 00:13:39,858
- I'm Chicken Joe, man.
- Thanks, Joe.

230
00:13:40,031 --> 00:13:43,398
Don't you ever, ever, do anything
like that in the contest, all right?

231
00:13:43,568 --> 00:13:44,830
- I'm in?
- Yeah, you're in.

232
00:13:45,002 --> 00:13:48,904
Because that was entertaining,
in a horrifying sort of way.

233
00:13:50,141 --> 00:13:51,631
Right on, dude.

234
00:13:52,844 --> 00:13:55,642
My name's Cody Maverick,
Shiverpool. You?

235
00:13:55,813 --> 00:13:58,145
No, I'm not from Shiverpool.

236
00:13:58,483 --> 00:14:02,078
- Where are you from?
- Dude, I'm from Lake Michigan.

237
00:14:02,253 --> 00:14:04,244
That's where I surf.
I was the only one...

238
00:14:05,723 --> 00:14:07,588
