324
00:20:20,898 --> 00:20:24,163
- Bring it on, pecker face. Let's go.
- Pecker face?

325
00:20:28,439 --> 00:20:29,770
It's mine!

326
00:20:39,850 --> 00:20:41,784
So, Cody, when you take
your first wave...

327
00:20:41,952 --> 00:20:44,420
...and the whole island's there
to watch, what'll it be like?

328
00:20:44,588 --> 00:20:47,421
It's gonna be amazing.
It'll be the best wave of my life.

329
00:20:47,591 --> 00:20:49,991
I hope the cameras are rolling
because you'll want to watch it...

330
00:20:50,160 --> 00:20:53,687
...over and over and over again.
It's gonna be awesome!

331
00:21:08,746 --> 00:21:10,145
I can't look.

332
00:21:10,648 --> 00:21:14,243
- Poor kid. He's... Poor kid.
- Wow! That was spectacular!

333
00:21:17,454 --> 00:21:20,014
I'm number one! The Tank!

334
00:21:54,458 --> 00:21:57,916
We're trying to get the details.
The lifeguard just pulled him in.

335
00:22:01,432 --> 00:22:04,890
That's what happens
when you take on the Tank, right?

336
00:22:06,704 --> 00:22:07,898
Cody, Cody!

337
00:22:08,072 --> 00:22:10,734
- How is he? Okay? What can I do?
- Yeah, he's okay.

338
00:22:10,908 --> 00:22:15,902
I can help. Except if there's blood.
Just the thought of blood makes me...

339
00:22:16,714 --> 00:22:18,739
Somebody help the chicken.

340
00:22:18,916 --> 00:22:21,407
- Tank, you okay?
- Tank needs fuel.

341
00:22:21,919 --> 00:22:24,114
Mikey, get the board, will you?

342
00:22:24,622 --> 00:22:26,749
Come on. Come on. Come on.

343
00:22:31,095 --> 00:22:36,226
- Did I win? I won, huh?
- You should've stayed in Antarctica.

344
00:22:37,234 --> 00:22:39,293
- Oh, wow.
- You're gonna be okay.

345
00:22:39,470 --> 00:22:43,668
Look at that.
There's pixies everywhere.

346
00:22:45,142 --> 00:22:48,634
What do you think about Cody going
into a contest and possibly winning?

347
00:22:48,812 --> 00:22:49,836
- You know, I'm...
- Ha.

348
00:22:50,014 --> 00:22:53,780
- Why did you just laugh?
- Because he keeps saying "possible."

349
00:22:53,951 --> 00:22:58,388
Like it's "possible" that you're gonna
win. And you're gonna do anything.

350
00:22:58,555 --> 00:23:01,922
- Really, what are the chances?
- They're high. Aren't they high?

351
00:23:02,226 --> 00:23:06,287
I mean, they're normal chances.
It's not like I'm, like, the underdog.

352
00:23:16,907 --> 00:23:21,640
Hey, Geek! Geek!
Get up and help me.

353
00:23:21,945 --> 00:23:23,412
Geek.

354
00:23:24,181 --> 00:23:25,739
Geek?

355
00:23:27,618 --> 00:23:31,816
Geek. Wake up! I need your help.

356
00:23:32,322 --> 00:23:34,620
Come on. Get off your lazy butt
and come and help me.

357
00:23:34,792 --> 00:23:36,453
Beautiful dream.

358
00:23:36,627 --> 00:23:39,926
- Did you ever know Sheila?
- No. I don't know Sheila.

359
00:23:40,097 --> 00:23:42,065
- Wait, wait, wait. What?
- What?

360
00:23:42,232 --> 00:23:43,221
Who's this guy?

361
00:23:43,400 --> 00:23:46,130
- He's a surfer. He's hurt.
- Who are all those guys?

362
00:23:46,303 --> 00:23:48,430
They're with him. Ignore them.

363
00:23:48,605 --> 00:23:50,334
- Come on.
- Lani, what are you doing?

364
00:23:50,507 --> 00:23:52,668
If you help him, they'll go away.

365
00:23:52,843 --> 00:23:55,368
- Hey! Get out of here!
- Help him!

366
00:23:56,180 --> 00:23:58,876
- Where do you want him?
- Nowhere. That's the whole point.

367
00:23:59,049 --> 00:24:02,075
- No outsiders. Come on.
- I know, I know, I know.

368
00:24:02,252 --> 00:24:06,586
This is an emergency. He went down
bad over the falls. I don't know if he...

369
00:24:09,893 --> 00:24:11,758
- And did he hit the reef?
- I don't know.

370
00:24:11,929 --> 00:24:13,419
I'm not sure. I got him after...

371
00:24:13,597 --> 00:24:15,394
- What, is he your boyfriend?
- No. No.

372
00:24:15,566 --> 00:24:19,127
Wait, wait, wait.
Looks like he stepped on a fire urchin.

373
00:24:19,970 --> 00:24:23,462
Stepped on me? Are you kidding?
This guy was dancing on me.

374
00:24:24,808 --> 00:24:28,608
Just look at this. Broken, broken,
gone, gone, broken, broken, broken...

375
00:24:28,779 --> 00:24:33,614
This is pretty bad.
This is really bad.

376
00:24:34,685 --> 00:24:36,482
- What... Cody!
- I hurt.

377
00:24:36,653 --> 00:24:40,054
- You're gonna be okay. What?
- Maybe I shouldn't have taken that out.

378
00:24:40,224 --> 00:24:42,124
Poison's released. Wow. Amazing.

379
00:24:42,292 --> 00:24:44,726
- What's amazing?
- That you're still alive.

380
00:24:44,895 --> 00:24:49,093
It's all right. I'm gonna fix you up.
I can fix your foot just fine.

381
00:24:49,333 --> 00:24:53,030
- Where is it? I've been looking...
- It's a saw. You just threw a saw.

382
00:24:53,203 --> 00:24:57,970
Don't let him move like that. He's
pushing the poison all over his body.

383
00:24:58,142 --> 00:25:00,372
- Come on, come on.
- I know he looks...

384
00:25:01,011 --> 00:25:02,478
Here it is.

385
00:25:03,547 --> 00:25:05,538
- What are you doing?
- What is he doing?

386
00:25:05,716 --> 00:25:07,013
This is a sure-fire cure.

387
00:25:07,184 --> 00:25:11,143
I learned it from an old medicine
man. It, well, works wonders.

388
00:25:11,355 --> 00:25:13,414
- What? No! Not that!
- Not what?

389
00:25:13,624 --> 00:25:15,819
What is he gonna... Gonna what?

390
00:25:16,460 --> 00:25:17,927
- Come on, now.
- Geek, stop.

391
00:25:18,095 --> 00:25:21,531
