392
00:25:21,698 --> 00:25:23,996
- Oh, my gosh, this is so gross.
- What is water sounds?

393
00:25:24,168 --> 00:25:27,899
- Come on. Here we go.
- No, no, no. You...

394
00:25:31,875 --> 00:25:34,935
Kid, you better keep your mouth shut.
See, what'd I tell you?

395
00:25:35,112 --> 00:25:38,172
Hold his foot still, Lani. Come on.
Knock him out or something.

396
00:25:38,348 --> 00:25:40,509
- I'm running on empty here.
- I'm trying!

397
00:25:45,422 --> 00:25:48,255
So how you been?

398
00:25:49,293 --> 00:25:51,761
Wow, sea urchin in the foot.
That sounds pretty nasty.

399
00:25:51,929 --> 00:25:52,918
Yeah.

400
00:25:53,096 --> 00:25:54,791
How do you cure something like that?

401
00:25:56,033 --> 00:25:57,364
You pee on it.

402
00:25:58,168 --> 00:26:00,636
- That's disgusting.
- I know!

403
00:26:00,804 --> 00:26:04,205
Hey. How long am I stuck
with this guy?

404
00:26:04,374 --> 00:26:06,239
- Because you know...
- Till he's better.

405
00:26:06,410 --> 00:26:11,006
Well, come back soon and,
please, bring me some clams.

406
00:26:11,181 --> 00:26:12,705
- No.
- I'm running low here.

407
00:26:12,883 --> 00:26:15,545
I can't keep doing this. You've got
to start taking care of yourself.

408
00:26:15,719 --> 00:26:17,380
- Oh, come on.
- Bye.

409
00:26:17,855 --> 00:26:22,349
- Bring me some more clams!
- Okay.

410
00:26:32,236 --> 00:26:34,932
If it's just as well with you,
I don't want to talk about Cody.

411
00:26:35,105 --> 00:26:37,198
He lost. That's it.
That's his problem. It's not mine.

412
00:26:37,374 --> 00:26:39,239
Aren't you concerned
about anybody's well-being...?

413
00:26:39,409 --> 00:26:42,173
The kid's fine. He was born in water.
He's a penguin, for crying out loud!

414
00:26:42,346 --> 00:26:45,110
- Did you see that wave hit him?
- That's the whole idea of surfing.

415
00:26:45,282 --> 00:26:48,410
- I care. I care!
- Mikey! Wait till you see this.

416
00:26:49,353 --> 00:26:51,412
Look at those little legs.
Stick, stick, stick, sticky.

417
00:26:51,588 --> 00:26:54,056
It's the way I walk. I'm constantly...

418
00:26:54,224 --> 00:26:57,193
- Boom-chicka-chicka...
- What's with the "boom-chicka-boom"?

419
00:26:57,828 --> 00:27:01,628
I can't stand blood.
I can't stand the sight of blood.

420
00:27:01,798 --> 00:27:05,632
I can't stand...
sight of blood. Cody!

421
00:27:06,837 --> 00:27:11,365
- Dude, have you seen my friend Cody?
- No.

422
00:27:11,909 --> 00:27:14,742
Cody? Cody?

423
00:27:17,281 --> 00:27:18,509
He's not under there.

424
00:27:19,016 --> 00:27:21,814
Cody!

425
00:27:23,654 --> 00:27:24,985
How's it going, man?

426
00:27:28,525 --> 00:27:29,992
So I woke up this morning.

427
00:27:30,160 --> 00:27:34,563
I didn't know where I was. It's never
a good place to be when you wake up.

428
00:27:34,731 --> 00:27:36,926
Come on. Get up.

429
00:27:37,100 --> 00:27:38,795
- I don't want to.
- Breakfast.

430
00:27:38,969 --> 00:27:42,405
- Wakey, wakey. Come on.
- I don't want to.

431
00:27:43,640 --> 00:27:45,039
- How's your foot?
- My foot...

432
00:27:45,208 --> 00:27:49,304
- My foot's fine, but my head.
- Good. Good. Come on, kid. Get up.

433
00:27:50,047 --> 00:27:51,776
What the...?

434
00:27:53,183 --> 00:27:55,310
Yeah, I think I got a concussion.

435
00:27:58,855 --> 00:28:02,086
You should meet my brother, Glen.
You guys would really hit it off.

436
00:28:02,259 --> 00:28:07,754
Oh, no. No. Where's my necklace?
Did you see my necklace? It's gotta...

437
00:28:08,565 --> 00:28:09,930
No, no.

438
00:28:10,100 --> 00:28:13,228
Big deal. Get yourself another one
at Reggie's trinket shops.

439
00:28:13,437 --> 00:28:16,634
It's not just some necklace, guy.
He gave it to me himself.

440
00:28:16,807 --> 00:28:20,072
- Who?
- Big Z. When he came to Shiverpool.

441
00:28:20,243 --> 00:28:22,677
That guy believed in me
when no one else did.

442
00:28:22,846 --> 00:28:24,814
He told me never to give up
and to find a way...

443
00:28:24,982 --> 00:28:27,450
...because that's what winners do.
- What winners do. Yeah.

444
00:28:27,617 --> 00:28:30,177
It's funny, you know,
what a loser I became.

445
00:28:30,354 --> 00:28:34,654
Who cares what Big Z said?
You got to...

446
00:28:35,792 --> 00:28:40,456
...you know, do things your own way.
- I don't have a way.

447
00:28:42,332 --> 00:28:47,964
You do now. Just follow this.
It'll take you back to North Beach.

448
00:28:48,472 --> 00:28:51,339
Okay, nice to meet you.
Good luck.

449
00:29:00,217 --> 00:29:01,309
What do I do now?

450
00:29:01,485 --> 00:29:04,977
I can't show my face on the beach.
I can't go home.

451
00:29:07,424 --> 00:29:11,417
You always visualize where you're
gonna be, what you're gonna do.

452
00:29:15,132 --> 00:29:16,929
This ain't it.

453
00:29:45,529 --> 00:29:48,464
- What are you doing here?
- Here.

454
00:29:48,632 --> 00:29:52,534
- Oh, man. Thank you, man. This...
- Yeah.

455
00:29:52,702 --> 00:29:54,294
