00:44:02,385 --> 00:44:05,354
...who's got to ride the thing.
- Fine. Thank you.

690
00:44:06,489 --> 00:44:10,721
- It's in there somewhere.
- Walk over there, please! Please.

691
00:44:11,193 --> 00:44:13,457
Don't cut yourself.

692
00:44:14,764 --> 00:44:16,322
So it's day three, yeah?

693
00:44:17,767 --> 00:44:20,759
I come across Pen Guans.

694
00:44:20,937 --> 00:44:24,373
I'm Chicken Joe. Joseph.
It's long for Joe.

695
00:44:24,941 --> 00:44:26,101
Sweet, man.

696
00:44:26,275 --> 00:44:30,541
And they treat me as their king
and put me in a hot tub.

697
00:44:31,113 --> 00:44:33,741
It is, I guess, their royal hot tub.

698
00:44:49,198 --> 00:44:51,428
It got kind of hot and steamy.

699
00:44:51,634 --> 00:44:54,159
But really opened up
my pores, you know?

700
00:44:56,372 --> 00:44:57,669
It was kind of cool.

701
00:44:57,840 --> 00:45:00,536
They served me food
while I was in there.

702
00:45:00,743 --> 00:45:03,405
It was like dinner and a show.

703
00:45:13,923 --> 00:45:17,586
As enjoyable as it was,
I still had a vision of my quest.

704
00:45:19,729 --> 00:45:23,563
Thank you. See you guys later.
I gotta get going.

705
00:45:25,401 --> 00:45:26,925
Not again.

706
00:45:29,105 --> 00:45:31,164
You know what else it was?
I had the board.

707
00:45:31,340 --> 00:45:33,035
The board was fine.
The board was great.

708
00:45:36,379 --> 00:45:39,439
- How's it going?
- It's going great, man. It's great.

709
00:45:39,915 --> 00:45:41,405
It did look a little rough.

710
00:45:41,584 --> 00:45:44,985
A little rough? The board looked
a little... It's a work in progress, bro.

711
00:45:45,154 --> 00:45:47,054
You think it's good enough
for the big waves?

712
00:45:47,223 --> 00:45:50,624
I think it's good enough
for any wave.

713
00:45:52,094 --> 00:45:53,584
Hang on.

714
00:45:54,463 --> 00:45:58,923
- Okay, let's say I'm a big wave.
- Hold on. No, no, no, no.

715
00:45:59,101 --> 00:46:00,932
- Hey, where you...
- Hold on!

716
00:46:01,103 --> 00:46:03,799
- Where are you going?
- It's my board, man, all right?

717
00:46:03,973 --> 00:46:06,942
Why don't you take your board
and go try it out?

718
00:46:07,109 --> 00:46:10,704
Maybe I will. Piece of junk. Watch!

719
00:46:13,949 --> 00:46:17,180
Nice ride, man.
Nice ride.

720
00:46:18,487 --> 00:46:20,387
This is supposed to be fun.

721
00:46:20,556 --> 00:46:24,287
I got three days until the contest.
I don't have time for fun.

722
00:46:24,927 --> 00:46:27,293
No time for fun, huh?

723
00:46:27,463 --> 00:46:28,930
- Hey, Cody!
- What?

724
00:46:29,098 --> 00:46:31,896
Bring me some clams
when you come back!

725
00:46:32,068 --> 00:46:34,764
I'm not coming back!

726
00:46:34,937 --> 00:46:37,405
- He'll be back.
- No, I won't!

727
00:46:37,573 --> 00:46:39,165
He'll be back.

728
00:46:39,608 --> 00:46:41,735
- You guys like barbecue?
- Yeah, sure.

729
00:46:41,911 --> 00:46:43,469
Got some wood here.

730
00:46:44,313 --> 00:46:47,749
I wasted my whole day and I have
nothing to show for it, which is...

731
00:46:52,621 --> 00:46:56,682
- I was just going to check on you...
- That's why you were...

732
00:46:56,859 --> 00:46:58,156
...and the Geek.

733
00:46:58,327 --> 00:47:01,626
- Listen. The Geek is Big Z.
- What?

734
00:47:01,797 --> 00:47:03,025
- I know.
- You know?

735
00:47:03,199 --> 00:47:05,133
- How did you find out?
- We went to the beach.

736
00:47:05,301 --> 00:47:06,529
- You got him to the beach?
- Yeah.

737
00:47:06,702 --> 00:47:09,330
I've been trying to get Z
out of that tree for 10 years...

738
00:47:09,505 --> 00:47:11,871
...and you got him all the way
down to the beach in one day?

739
00:47:12,041 --> 00:47:13,565
This is fantastic!

740
00:47:15,878 --> 00:47:20,975
It's amazing!
Do you want to go somewhere fun?

741
00:47:21,183 --> 00:47:26,018
Do you want to go somewhere
really, really fun?

742
00:47:26,188 --> 00:47:28,816
Unless you want...
Did you want to get back to Big Z?

743
00:47:28,991 --> 00:47:31,357
- I'm sorry. I shouldn't have invited you.
- No, no, no.

744
00:47:31,527 --> 00:47:34,462
- What? Okay. No?
- No, look. I want to have fun.

745
00:47:34,630 --> 00:47:36,894
- Okay.
- Do I need mints or something?

746
00:47:37,066 --> 00:47:40,035
- You tell me.
- No, you won't need mints.

747
00:47:40,769 --> 00:47:44,569
Z used to carry us up here on his
shoulders. We'd have so much fun.

748
00:47:44,740 --> 00:47:47,368
- It's one of my favorite spots.
- Really?

749
00:47:47,576 --> 00:47:50,477
- Boy, to be 8 years old again.
- What is this?

750
00:47:50,646 --> 00:47:52,637
You don't want to
get all cut up, do you?

751
00:47:52,815 --> 00:47:54,146
Hold on. What are you doing?

752
00:47:54,316 --> 00:47:56,580
No, no, no. I'm out of here.
I'm better off...

753
00:48:08,097 --> 00:48:10,088
It's going down! No, no, no!

754
00:48:14,403 --> 00:48:18,464
- This is insane!
- Stop fighting it, Cody! Just let go!

755
00:48:20,576 --> 00:48:22,203
All right!

756
00:48:26,649 --> 00:48:29,311
Now I'm in front of you.
What's going on now?

757
00:48:29,485 --> 00:48:30,975
It's not a race!

758
00:48:39,762 --> 00:48:42,663
Okay, wait, don't take the left...
Cody!

759
00:48:47,336 --> 00:48:51,363
- Give up, slowpoke! It's over with now!
- Not for long!

760
00:48:51,707 --> 00:48:53,902
Give up now, sucker!

761
00:48:58,080 --> 00:49:01,413
- I beat you!
- Congratulations, you sure did.

762
00:49:01,584 --> 00:49:03,142
You should probably
get out of there.

763
00:49:03,319 --> 00:49:05,583
Why is that? This stuff is...
Look at me. It's so beautiful.

764
00:49:05,754 --> 00:49:07,346
Look at it. What is this stuff?

765
00:49:07,523 --> 00:49:10,356
See those things up above you?
They're glowworms.

766
00:49:10,526 --> 00:49:14,986
So you're right beneath them.
Yeah, that's poop.

767
00:49:25,007 --> 00:49:28,773
You know how some stinks stink
and other stinks smell good?

768
00:49:28,944 --> 00:49:31,208
- Yeah.
- This is, like, a good stink.

769
00:49:31,380 --> 00:49:32,369
A good stink?

770
00:49:33,048 --> 00:49:34,777
Can I tell you something personal?

771
00:49:34,950 --> 00:49:37,214
We're in the shower together.
You can say whatever you want.

772
00:49:37,386 --> 00:49:41,823
I'm serious. I'm really, really
jealous of you.

773
00:49:41,991 --> 00:49:43,117
Why?

774
00:49:43,292 --> 00:49:47,160
I couldn't get Z off his butt
for the last 10 years...

775
00:49:47,329 --> 00:49:49,854
...and then you come along and...

776
00:49:50,032 --> 00:49:52,796
He must really think a lot of you.

777
00:49:52,968 --> 00:49:56,529
I don't know. I've been a jerk to him.
I don't know what he thinks.

778
00:49:56,705 --> 00:49:58,798
- You haven't.
- I have. I've been a jerk.

779
00:50:00,175 --> 00:50:03,542
- I have.
- Then go not be a jerk.

780
00:50:04,213 --> 00:50:05,976
What does it matter to you anyways?

781
00:50:06,148 --> 00:50:08,844
He's my uncle.
He's the only family I've got.

782
00:50:18,093 --> 00:50:19,492
Okay.

783
00:51:21,924 --> 00:51:23,653
Z? No.

784
00:51:24,326 --> 00:51:28,592
No, no, no, don't you do it.
Z, don't do it. No.

785
00:51:28,764 --> 00:51:30,629
- No.
- Let's see here.

786
00:51:30,799 --> 00:51:32,664
- I swear...
- It's stronger than I thought.

787
00:51:32,835 --> 00:51:36,168
...if you break it...
- Should've been broken by now.

788
00:51:36,338 --> 00:51:39,000
Come on! Come on!

789
00:51:42,778 --> 00:51:44,439
Look at that.

790
00:51:46,048 --> 00:51:49,677
That's the best place
in the world to be, in the tube.

791
00:51:49,852 --> 00:51:50,876
Really?

792
00:51:51,053 --> 00:51:55,456
Yeah. Better than winning,
the trophy, all that stuff.

793
00:51:56,291 --> 00:51:59,658
Tube riding
is the ultimate thing in surfing...

794
00:51:59,828 --> 00:52:02,023
...to ride inside the wave
and make it out of it.

795
00:52:02,197 --> 00:52:03,789
It's all we want to do every day.

796
00:52:03,966 --> 00:52:06,901
It's almost impossible to describe.

797
00:52:07,069 --> 00:52:09,003
There's nothing I can compare it to.

798
00:52:09,171 --> 00:52:13,631
It's a feeling that not too many people
will experience...

799
00:52:14,143 --> 00:52:15,804
...so it's special in that sense.

800
00:52:15,978 --> 00:52:17,343
Then you try to remember it.

801
00:52:17,513 --> 00:52:20,448
Like, "I wish I could remember that,"
or "I wish I could get that again."

802
00:52:20,616 --> 00:52:22,277
It's so addicting.

803
00:52:22,651 --> 00:52:26,485
Once you get inside
you never want to get out.

804
00:52:26,688 --> 00:52:32,149
- Wow. That's amazing.
- Yeah, man. Nothing like it.

805
00:52:32,327 --> 00:52:37,822
So, that aside, how many points
would you get for getting tubed?

806
00:52:38,033 --> 00:52:40,331
Like, what does it depend on
for the contest?

807
00:52:40,502 --> 00:52:42,732
- Points?
- What?

808
00:52:42,938 --> 00:52:45,429
You know who you
sound like right now?

809
00:52:45,607 --> 00:52:47,370
I promote happiness!

810
00:52:47,543 --> 00:52:51,172
Can you see the happiness emanating
from me? What's wrong with you?

811
00:52:51,346 --> 00:52:53,177
- We're live.
- Good. Good.

812
00:52:53,348 --> 00:52:57,648
I have to say, I have no doubt
that this year's Big Z Memorial...

813
00:52:57,820 --> 00:52:59,151
...is gonna be the best ever.

814
00:53:00,556 --> 00:53:03,047
With the competition
just one day away...

815
00:53:03,225 --> 00:53:07,719
...the excitement is definitely building
here on Pen Gu Island.

816
00:53:28,083 --> 00:53:31,450
That didn't take too long.
I feel lightheaded.

817
00:53:31,620 --> 00:53:32,848
So get this.

818
00:53:33,188 --> 00:53:37,249
On my search for Cody,
I bump into my hot tub buddies again.

819
00:53:38,594 --> 00:53:40,789
I get it. You guys look hungry.

820
00:53:40,963 --> 00:53:44,194
You've probably got
the munchies or something.

821
00:53:46,268 --> 00:53:48,532
Squidito on el stickito?

822
00:53:58,347 --> 00:54:02,215
Check it out! Dude,
have you seen my friend Cody?

823
00:54:02,384 --> 00:54:05,114
He's kind of like a penguin.

824
00:54:05,287 --> 00:54:08,381
He's got a lot of black on him,
a lot of white.

825
00:54:08,557 --> 00:54:12,049
- How did you learn how to surf?
- I saw Big Z do it, actually.

826
00:54:12,227 --> 00:54:14,127
I don't think you were born yet.

827
00:54:14,296 --> 00:54:16,696
- I wasn't?
- No, I don't think so.

828
00:54:16,965 --> 00:54:21,732
Lani? I like her when
she teaches us because...

829
00:54:21,904 --> 00:54:23,633
Smudge! Not another one!

830
00:54:23,805 --> 00:54:26,330
I think he really has to go
to the bathroom right now.

831
00:54:26,975 --> 00:54:28,704
What's next? The board is done.

832
00:54:28,877 --> 00:54:30,777
- The board is done?
- The board is done.

833
00:54:30,946 --> 00:54:34,848
- Well, let's do some training.
- Finally!

834
00:54:35,183 --> 00:54:38,277
- Can we get a shot of you...
- You've got to get it in a long shot.

835
00:54:39,321 --> 00:54:41,812
Hey, Z! Come on!

836
00:54:41,990 --> 00:54:43,924
- Where you going?
- I thought we were going to train.

837
00:54:44,092 --> 00:54:47,550
Not in the water. Jeez.
What are you thinking?

838
00:54:48,964 --> 00:54:52,092
- You want to surf like Big Z used to?
- Yeah.

839
00:54:52,267 --> 00:54:54,963
I've got some tests here
to figure out your potential.

840
00:54:55,137 --> 00:54:57,662
- Let's do it.
- No, put them on your eyes.

841
00:54:57,839 --> 00:55:00,330
- Like this.
- On my eyes.

842
00:55:03,045 --> 00:55:06,071
- Take it, Cody.
- Can we do some training, seriously?

843
00:55:06,248 --> 00:55:08,375
What are you talking about?
What do you think we're doing?

844
00:55:08,550 --> 00:55:10,575
Acting like nutjobs.
That's what I think we're doing.

845
00:55:10,752 --> 00:55:13,152
Yeah, good. You're learning!

846
00:55:13,322 --> 00:55:15,347
And a big set comes in.

847
00:55:17,726 --> 00:55:19,421
Wipeout!

848
00:55:19,761 --> 00:55:21,661
- That's it!
- Take it easy!

849
00:55:22,130 --> 00:55:23,722
This is getting ridiculous.

850
00:55:23,899 --> 00:55:25,332
- You having fun?
- I hate you.

851
00:55:26,435 --> 00:55:27,868
Big, you know, slow:

852
00:55:29,771 --> 00:55:32,865
He does this flip over the top.
All right, now you go.

853
00:55:34,977 --> 00:55:37,878
No joy, man. No joy. Fail.

854
00:55:38,847 --> 00:55:43,511
I'm starting to see it, man. I think
I know what you're talking about.

855
00:55:44,453 --> 00:55:47,513
That's great. As long as
we're all having fun, right?

856
00:55:47,789 --> 00:55:51,987
Z, wake up. Wake up, Z. Z!

857
00:56:00,602 --> 00:56:02,570
Hey, Z, breakfast!

858
00:56:04,573 --> 00:56:05,938
Not a chance.

859
00:56:06,274 --> 00:56:09,869
- Four, three, two...
- You gotta get up early in the morning...

860
00:56:10,445 --> 00:56:11,537
...one.

861
00:56:20,489 --> 00:56:21,478
That is fun.

862
00:56:21,657 --> 00:56:24,592
- You're having fun?
- I am. Yes. Now I am.

863
00:56:25,160 --> 00:56:26,354
Then, Cody...

864
00:56:26,528 --> 00:56:28,189
...you passed!
- What?

865
00:56:28,363 --> 00:56:30,854
You did it! You're ready! Let's surf!

866
00:56:31,033 --> 00:56:35,561
Don't play me, Z. We're surfing?
Yes! Yes!

867
00:56:46,248 --> 00:56:47,715
Hey, check it...

868
00:56:54,423 --> 00:56:56,550
I didn't know you could surf!

869
00:57:02,798 --> 00:57:04,026
Relax!

870
00:57:04,199 --> 00:57:07,896
Long, slow, smooth.

871
00:57:08,070 --> 00:57:09,901
- Like making the board!
- There you go.

872
00:57:10,072 --> 00:57:13,007
- All right. Okay.
- Feels good, yeah?

873
00:57:24,219 --> 00:57:29,088
- You're in the water, Z!
- Come on out. Get wet! Come on!

874
00:57:33,562 --> 00:57:37,259
Lani, thank you.

875
00:57:43,171 --> 00:57:44,934
Look at that!

876
00:57:58,053 --> 00:58:01,716
- Nice! That's it! Nice.
- Great ride!

877
00:58:27,082 --> 00:58:28,879
Big Z is back!

878
00:58:40,195 --> 00:58:42,663
This is what it's all about.

879
00:58:43,465 --> 00:58:45,990
What could be better than this?

880
00:59:12,861 --> 00:59:15,455
I need some help
on this landing for the high note

881
00:59:19,968 --> 00:59:22,766
Nice. Nice.

882
00:59:23,138 --> 00:59:25,231
- Is that the only song that you know?
- Pretty much.

883
00:59:25,407 --> 00:59:27,875
You want to hear it again?
It goes like this.

884
00:59:28,109 --> 00:59:30,771
No? Okay. I got you there, didn't I?

885
00:59:30,946 --> 00:59:34,609
I must say you were
quite amazing out there today.

886
00:59:34,783 --> 00:59:37,547
- You weren't so bad yourself, kiddo.
- Thanks to this guy.

887
00:59:38,386 --> 00:59:42,948
- I just pointed you in a direction.
- Question, Z.

888
00:59:44,125 --> 00:59:46,150
- Change your mind about the song?
- No, no, no.

889
00:59:46,328 --> 00:59:47,795
Here, it goes something like this...

890
00:59:47,963 --> 00:59:50,693
I was wondering if you could come
watch me ride tomorrow.

891
00:59:52,300 --> 00:59:54,700
Yeah, yeah. We'll both ride, man.

892
00:59:54,870 --> 00:59:59,534
- No, not just... In the contest.
- Contest? What contest?

893
00:59:59,708 --> 01:00:01,903
The Big Z Memorial.
Remember that one?

894
01:00:02,077 --> 01:00:03,704
I know I'm asking a lot...

895
01:00:03,879 --> 01:00:06,279
...but it would really, really be...

896
01:00:06,448 --> 01:00:09,576
...the biggest thing in the world
to me if you could come.

897
01:00:11,653 --> 01:00:14,486
- You still want to be a part of that?
- Absolutely.

898
01:00:15,056 --> 01:00:19,516
- Why do you want me there anyway?
- I thought you'd want to be there.

899
01:00:19,694 --> 01:00:22,663
- I don't know why it's a big deal.
- It's no big deal.

900
01:00:22,964 --> 01:00:24,761
Why won't you come?

901
01:00:25,000 --> 01:00:26,262
- I'm not coming.
- Why?

902
01:00:26,434 --> 01:00:28,231
- Give it a rest.
- It's getting cold, guys.

903
01:00:28,403 --> 01:00:29,961
- Tell me why you're hiding.
- Hiding?

904
01:00:30,138 --> 01:00:32,504
- Why are you hiding?
- I'll have to eat all this by myself.

905
01:00:32,674 --> 01:00:34,801
Why didn't you come back
after you fell off the wave?

906
01:00:35,877 --> 01:00:38,004
That wave.

907
01:00:39,848 --> 01:00:44,979
That last day, winning had
become everything to me.

908
01:00:45,320 --> 01:00:46,947
I knew I was gonna beat Tank.

909
01:00:48,256 --> 01:00:54,422
But then, you know,
he starts to surf circles around me.

910
01:00:54,596 --> 01:00:57,656
I saw what he was doing.
I couldn't do what he was doing.

911
01:00:58,466 --> 01:01:00,764
Times had changed.

912
01:01:01,870 --> 01:01:04,703
I didn't want to walk back
on that beach with all my fans there.

913
01:01:04,873 --> 01:01:09,333
A loser. Everyone looking
at Big Z, the loser, the has-been.

914
01:01:09,911 --> 01:01:11,572
So...

915
01:01:19,821 --> 01:01:22,722
Big Z's dead,
and that's how it's gonna stay.

916
01:01:23,358 --> 01:01:25,519
Let me play you that song.

917
01:01:26,728 --> 01:01:29,697
What about "never give up"?
What about "find a way"?

918
01:01:30,031 --> 01:01:34,968
- You're giving up. You're giving up!
- Yeah, I'm giving up. That's my way.

919
01:01:35,437 --> 01:01:38,702
- Giving up.
- I thought you were the one guy.

920
01:01:38,873 --> 01:01:41,842
You don't like it, find your own way.

921
01:01:43,611 --> 01:01:45,135
Leave me out of it.

922
01:01:45,947 --> 01:01:47,539
Leave me out of it.

923
01:02:15,110 --> 01:02:17,601
I messed up.
I'm just...

924
01:02:17,812 --> 01:02:19,803
I'm... not good.

925
01:02:20,215 --> 01:02:22,945
This is when I needed someone.
I needed him.

926
01:02:23,985 --> 01:02:26,886
It's hard enough
losing one dad, but...

927
01:02:27,956 --> 01:02:30,390
- What do you mean by...?
- Nothing.

928
01:02:30,592 --> 01:02:32,890
Nothing, man. Forget it.

929
01:02:47,475 --> 01:02:49,773
Peaceful. Peaceful.
I'm in peace. I come in peace.

930
01:02:49,978 --> 01:02:51,138
- Cody!
- Joe!

931
01:02:51,546 --> 01:02:54,845
- I've been looking everywhere for you!
- You've been looking for me?

932
01:02:55,016 --> 01:02:57,849
I didn't lose you on the whale.
I'm not gonna lose you now.

933
01:02:58,019 --> 01:03:01,455
- Thank you. Seriously, thank you.
- Radical.

934
01:03:03,691 --> 01:03:06,159
They're starting!
Cody, we gotta go! Come on!

935
01:03:06,361 --> 01:03:07,828
Wait a minute. Joe?

936
01:03:07,996 --> 01:03:09,088
Surfers riding...

937
01:03:09,264 --> 01:03:12,290
I'm sorry. Watch this, dude.
I can speak their language.

938
01:03:16,204 --> 01:03:19,401
I totally need my board. I don't
know where it is. I gotta go find it.

939
01:03:19,574 --> 01:03:21,769
- I'll see you in the lineup.
- See you, Joe.

940
01:03:21,943 --> 01:03:24,468
- This is gonna be fun, huh?
- See you.

941
01:03:26,081 --> 01:03:29,778
The tenth annual Big Z
is about to get underway...

942
01:03:29,951 --> 01:03:32,749
...and, whoa, it is the day of days.

943
01:03:32,921 --> 01:03:36,118
Big mountainous bombs
marching into our coastline.

944
01:03:36,424 --> 01:03:40,053
Kelly Slater, on a danger level,
one to ten, give me a number.

945
01:03:40,228 --> 01:03:41,217
Twenty.

946
01:03:41,396 --> 01:03:43,421
- Wow. Rob?
- There'll be blood.

947
01:03:43,598 --> 01:03:45,532
I'm scared, and I'm in the booth!

948
01:03:46,501 --> 01:03:48,662
- What are you doing here?
- Mike.

949
01:03:48,837 --> 01:03:51,101
You're gonna kill yourself.
Don't do this to yourself.

950
01:03:51,272 --> 01:03:52,603
Look what happened last time.

951
01:03:53,308 --> 01:03:55,572
- It's good to see you back.
- Are you serious?

952
01:03:55,743 --> 01:03:57,267
You're gonna be
a real crowd pleaser.

953
01:03:57,445 --> 01:03:59,777
I'm telling you,
these people are gonna eat you up.

954
01:03:59,948 --> 01:04:03,440
- I'll be expecting big things from you.
- Thank you.

955
01:04:03,618 --> 01:04:05,848
People, big announcement.
Cody Maverick, he's back.

956
01:04:06,020 --> 01:04:07,351
The Wipeout King is back...

957
01:04:07,522 --> 01:04:09,615
...and I'm gonna tell you,
start looking for the sharks.

958
01:04:09,791 --> 01:04:11,850
They'll be circling because
there's gonna be blood.

959
01:04:12,026 --> 01:04:13,459
Spectacular carnage today.

960
01:04:13,628 --> 01:04:17,564
Thank you! Reggie Belafonte. Little
guy, big hair, big thoughts, big heart.

961
01:04:26,441 --> 01:04:30,400
Look at this.
You're going down, snowflake.

962
01:04:31,579 --> 01:04:34,810
I'm gonna make you wish
you were never even hatched.

963
01:04:35,950 --> 01:04:38,475
You want to see my trophies?

964
01:04:48,096 --> 01:04:49,927
Arnold, no.

965
01:04:55,937 --> 01:04:58,929
About 24 surfers
battling their way out to the...

966
01:04:59,974 --> 01:05:02,772
Good golly! Make that 18.

967
01:05:06,047 --> 01:05:08,447
Rob, after such a heavy wipeout
earlier in the week...

968
01:05:08,616 --> 01:05:10,641
...what do you think is going
through Maverick's mind?

969
01:05:10,818 --> 01:05:14,811
He's gonna have to stay focused and
channel that energy into good places.

970
01:05:15,123 --> 01:05:16,784
When are you gonna get a life?

971
01:05:19,194 --> 01:05:20,957
You are a nobody.

972
01:05:22,230 --> 01:05:24,460
You should've stayed
in Antarctica, kid.

973
01:05:49,023 --> 01:05:51,890
He made it! Yeah, good.

974
01:05:52,060 --> 01:05:55,928
What an amazing first ride
mind-blower from Maverick.

975
01:06:01,636 --> 01:06:03,297
Did you guys see that?

976
01:06:03,471 --> 01:06:06,565
Man. I thought I was gonna lose it,
and then I just...

977
01:06:07,809 --> 01:06:10,710
I just let go, you know.
I let go, and there it was.

978
01:06:11,980 --> 01:06:14,642
Wow, it's been an amazing day...

979
01:06:14,816 --> 01:06:16,807
...of shredding in less than
stellar conditions...

980
01:06:16,985 --> 01:06:19,920
...but I never would have guessed
our three finalists.

981
01:06:20,088 --> 01:06:22,215
Well, Sal, it's no surprise
that Tank Evans...

982
01:06:22,390 --> 01:06:25,484
...has just breezed his way
into the finals.

983
01:06:25,660 --> 01:06:29,960
And Cody Maverick, from a horrible
wipeout a few days ago to this.

984
01:06:32,333 --> 01:06:35,564
And Chicken Joe from Sheboygan.
Who would have guessed it?

985
01:06:36,204 --> 01:06:39,503
I have never seen a finals like this.

986
01:06:40,642 --> 01:06:43,270
- We're in the finals, Joe.
- No way! We get to surf some more?

987
01:06:43,444 --> 01:06:46,777
Isn't it exciting?
Look at that. This is great, huh?

988
01:06:47,048 --> 01:06:50,381
You know, you should know this.
The Tank loves you.

989
01:06:51,286 --> 01:06:53,720
Looks like this will be
the easiest year ever.

990
01:06:54,789 --> 01:06:57,815
No way. Cody, did you hear that?
It's gonna be easy.

991
01:06:58,559 --> 01:07:01,221
Are you loving this?

992
01:07:03,631 --> 01:07:05,565
So who would you like
to see win the trophy?

993
01:07:05,733 --> 01:07:08,327
It's not so important to me.

994
01:07:08,503 --> 01:07:11,165
Friends are better than anything
in the world.

995
01:07:11,339 --> 01:07:12,533
Friends are forever.

996
01:07:13,174 --> 01:07:16,473
Trophies, you never know
what they can have happen to them.

997
01:07:17,745 --> 01:07:20,578
- That was awesome, mate.
- Muy impresivo, my friend.

998
01:07:20,748 --> 01:07:22,079
Thank you, bro. Thanks.

999
01:07:22,850 --> 01:07:24,249
- Finals.
- Hey!

1000
01:07:24,419 --> 01:07:27,081
Yeah. I know. I can't even...

1001
01:07:28,022 --> 01:07:30,684
I think I can win this thing.
It's too much right now.

1002
01:07:30,858 --> 01:07:33,349
- Well, that's all you came for.
- What?

1003
01:07:33,528 --> 01:07:36,622
- What is that supposed to mean?
- You made it pretty clear last night...

1004
01:07:36,798 --> 01:07:38,857
...that winning's more important
to you than Z or me.

1005
01:07:39,033 --> 01:07:41,433
But, hey, maybe you'll get to take
your stupid trophy home.

1006
01:07:41,602 --> 01:07:44,002
- Lani. Come on.
- Come here, you!

1007
01:07:44,472 --> 01:07:45,803
How about this, huh?

1008
01:07:45,973 --> 01:07:51,036
Let me tell you something. You win
this thing, we're going places!

1009
01:07:51,245 --> 01:07:54,146
Look at this kid.
He is a champ!

1010
01:08:03,725 --> 01:08:07,889
Tank, nine-time defending champion.
He will roll on you.

1011
01:08:08,062 --> 01:08:11,554
Expect him to win this thing. It's
basically a contest for second place.

1012
01:08:11,733 --> 01:08:16,397
First, I'm gonna take you down.
Then I'm gonna fry the chicken.

1013
01:08:18,573 --> 01:08:21,474
That cloud looks just like a kitten.

1014
01:08:34,989 --> 01:08:36,786
Maverick and Evans take off.

1015
01:08:37,492 --> 01:08:38,516
Mine!

1016
01:08:38,693 --> 01:08:41,025
And it's Evans dropping in.

1017
01:08:43,798 --> 01:08:46,790
And Tank's playing games,
blocking Maverick's every move.

1018
01:08:47,735 --> 01:08:49,259
Maverick sticks a rail.

1019
01:08:50,471 --> 01:08:55,170
Tank Evans down!
I have never, ever seen this before!

1020
01:08:57,145 --> 01:08:58,635
But I'd love to see it again.

1021
01:08:58,813 --> 01:09:02,442
Cody trying to take back the wave
that Tank snaked from him.

1022
01:09:02,617 --> 01:09:04,915
Evans toying with him,
not paying attention.

1023
01:09:05,086 --> 01:09:07,316
And there's the outside rail.
Evans goes down.

1024
01:09:07,488 --> 01:09:12,016
And it's Maverick with this new-school
move. We'll call it "The Maverick."

1025
01:09:17,832 --> 01:09:20,995
And look at this.
Maverick scoring big.

1026
01:09:22,069 --> 01:09:26,506
Oh, it's so cute.
It's got little paws and the whiskers.

1027
01:09:29,477 --> 01:09:32,310
Chicken Joe
with a no-paddle drop-in!

1028
01:09:33,981 --> 01:09:36,814
- Here we go!
- Nobody needs to help this chicken.

1029
01:09:37,852 --> 01:09:39,080
I'm flying!

1030
01:09:40,655 --> 01:09:45,756
Maverick and Joe tied, and no score
for Tank Evans? Unbelievable.

1031
01:09:47,361 --> 01:09:51,229
Surfers, this is your final wave!

1032
01:09:51,399 --> 01:09:55,733
- Joe, this is it. This wave wins it.
- Yeah, man!

1033
01:09:57,738 --> 01:10:02,072
This wave is stacking up
to be a beautiful tube.

1034
01:10:02,710 --> 01:10:05,941
Maverick should score big
on this one!

1035
01:10:07,782 --> 01:10:10,114
But wait! Evans drops in.

1036
01:10:10,284 --> 01:10:13,879
It looks like Evans
is gonna take out the chicken.

1037
01:10:19,293 --> 01:10:20,624
What's Maverick doing?

1038
01:10:20,795 --> 01:10:23,696
- Go, Joe, go!
- Got it! Let's go!

1039
01:10:23,865 --> 01:10:26,766
I don't believe this.
This contest was Maverick's to win.

1040
01:10:26,968 --> 01:10:30,699
Now Evans pushing Maverick out
of bounds and into The Boneyards.

1041
01:10:43,417 --> 01:10:46,250
- Tank, look out!
- You look out!

1042
01:11:21,622 --> 01:11:22,611
Code!

1043
01:11:25,159 --> 01:11:26,148
Z!

1044
01:11:30,298 --> 01:11:32,198
- Cody, come on.
- Z!

1045
01:11:32,366 --> 01:11:36,132
Paddle! Come on! Dig! Faster!
Come on. Dig!

1046
01:11:37,371 --> 01:11:39,771
Don't dig! Don't dig!

1047
01:11:39,941 --> 01:11:41,033
What?

1048
01:11:41,709 --> 01:11:44,234
Let the wave carry you!

1049
01:11:44,879 --> 01:11:46,540
You're gonna have to time it!

1050
01:11:47,081 --> 01:11:50,209
You're gonna come right here,
right to me!

1051
01:11:53,754 --> 01:11:55,745
Five... four...

1052
01:11:55,990 --> 01:11:58,584
Three... two... one.

1053
01:12:03,664 --> 01:12:05,131
Z!

1054
01:12:20,414 --> 01:12:21,972
Where's Cody?

1055
01:12:26,354 --> 01:12:28,413
Don't touch it! Don't touch that!

1056
01:12:28,589 --> 01:12:31,683
This is a reminder
of the young surfer...

1057
01:12:31,859 --> 01:12:36,922
...who gave his life
for the sport he loved.

1058
01:12:41,135 --> 01:12:42,932
There you are.

1059
01:12:47,708 --> 01:12:51,007
I can't believe it! I can't believe it.

1060
01:12:52,213 --> 01:12:53,544
You came back.

1061
01:12:54,048 --> 01:12:56,710
You saved my life, man.
Thank you.

1062
01:12:56,884 --> 01:13:00,251
Hey, hey, come on.
You're gonna tip us!

1063
01:13:02,089 --> 01:13:04,717
Well, I lost.

1064
01:13:06,394 --> 01:13:08,089
Me too.

1065
01:13:10,231 --> 01:13:13,223
Come on. Let's go, loser.

1066
01:13:14,068 --> 01:13:15,433
You want to help me out here?

1067
01:13:15,603 --> 01:13:20,734
You know the routine. Come on. Long.
That's it. Smooth, you know. Come on.

1068
01:13:21,075 --> 01:13:26,069
Young Joey MacEnroe
was a beacon for a new generation.

1069
01:13:26,247 --> 01:13:29,216
May he rest in peace.

1070
01:13:31,118 --> 01:13:34,178
So, what am I bid for the board?
Who'll give me 30? 30, come on.

1071
01:13:34,355 --> 01:13:36,516
- Don't touch his stuff, man.
- Pal, if you want to bid...

1072
01:13:36,691 --> 01:13:38,886
- Give me that.
- Hey...!

1073
01:13:44,632 --> 01:13:46,361
Hey. Hey, everyone.

1074
01:13:47,368 --> 01:13:49,666
- How you been?
- Oh, my gosh!

1075
01:13:49,870 --> 01:13:52,031
- Yeah...
- Hey, man, that's Z.

1076
01:13:52,239 --> 01:13:53,797
...that's me.

1077
01:13:53,974 --> 01:13:56,204
Skank, what's happening, man?

1078
01:13:56,377 --> 01:13:59,039
Got a little sand
in your egg sac there, fella.

1079
01:13:59,213 --> 01:14:01,545
- Where have you been, Z?
- What happened?

1080
01:14:02,416 --> 01:14:03,747
Oh, you know...

1081
01:14:05,720 --> 01:14:10,714
...I got lost for a little while.
But that kid there, Cody...

1082
01:14:11,926 --> 01:14:14,759
...he pointed the way back.

1083
01:14:25,606 --> 01:14:27,801
Could you please shut that off?
Could you give me a minute?

1084
01:14:34,181 --> 01:14:36,115
Check it out! How about this?

1085
01:14:36,283 --> 01:14:38,751
You want to talk about talent scout?
People find talent.

1086
01:14:38,953 --> 01:14:44,619
I bring them back from the dead.
The now living legend, ladies and...

1087
01:14:44,792 --> 01:14:46,123
- Shut up.
- What? Shut up?

1088
01:14:46,293 --> 01:14:50,286
I'm not a legend. I'm a guy looking for
some nice waves, some good friends.

1089
01:14:50,798 --> 01:14:54,427
Hey, guys, the swell is happening
over on the north shore!

1090
01:14:54,602 --> 01:14:55,967
I'm right behind you, Z.

1091
01:14:56,137 --> 01:14:57,468
Ouch, that hurt.

1092
01:14:59,607 --> 01:15:03,873
Come back here!
You don't just walk away! Come on!

1093
01:15:05,246 --> 01:15:06,611
He's taking this loss pretty hard.

1094
01:15:06,781 --> 01:15:09,750
Tank, how does it feel
to lose after nine time...

1095
01:15:11,385 --> 01:15:14,616
I wasn't kissing her.
You can't have her!

1096
01:15:18,159 --> 01:15:19,148
Can we get a few words?

1097
01:15:19,326 --> 01:15:21,988
You gave up the trophy to help Joe.
What's that about?

1098
01:15:22,163 --> 01:15:25,064
You know, Rob,
that's what friends do.

1099
01:15:25,232 --> 01:15:28,360
- How's it feel to win, Joe?
- I won?

1100
01:15:28,536 --> 01:15:31,835
Come on! I'll tell my mom.
Gimme. Gimme!

1101
01:15:33,507 --> 01:15:36,374
Oh, Lia! Oh, Lia.

1102
01:15:36,544 --> 01:15:40,139
Don't you walk away from me!
I am Reggie Belafon...

1103
01:15:41,649 --> 01:15:45,176
Turn that thing off.
Mikey! You are so fired!

1104
01:15:45,786 --> 01:15:48,414
I can't imagine a better day.

1105
01:15:54,595 --> 01:15:58,588
Dude, this... This whole
experience has just been...

1106
01:15:58,799 --> 01:16:01,700
It's amazing. Z?

1107
01:16:01,869 --> 01:16:06,772
I don't think I've ever had
a better friend to me in my life.

1108
01:16:06,941 --> 01:16:10,604
It's just really cool
to have everything I need.

1109
01:16:11,478 --> 01:16:13,946
- Don't do it. Help!
- Arnold!

1110
01:16:14,114 --> 01:16:17,515
To be honest, man, I'm kind of, like,
bored of talking about myself.

1111
01:16:17,685 --> 01:16:21,348
So, is that cool?
You guys got what you need?

1112
01:16:21,522 --> 01:16:23,820
- We got it.
- All right. Be good!

1113
01:16:32,433 --> 01:16:33,957
Cowabunga!

1114
01:17:42,002 --> 01:17:43,936
Of course we're proud of him!

1115
01:17:44,104 --> 01:17:45,935
What mother wouldn't be
proud of him?

1116
01:17:46,106 --> 01:17:48,370
We're so full of proudness.

1117
01:17:48,542 --> 01:17:50,442
You know what?
He followed his dream...

1118
01:17:50,611 --> 01:17:54,377
...and he went out there, and now
he's coming home with the trophy.

1119
01:17:54,548 --> 01:17:56,539
I can't wait to see his trophy.

1120
01:17:56,717 --> 01:17:58,708
There's not really a trophy.

1121
01:17:59,453 --> 01:18:01,887
Is there, like, a big shell
or something like that?

1122
01:18:02,056 --> 01:18:04,786
There's no shell. There's no trophy.
Well, he didn't win.

1123
01:18:04,959 --> 01:18:05,983
What?

1124
01:18:06,360 --> 01:18:09,352
How bad was it?
Did he get smoked?

1125
01:18:09,563 --> 01:18:12,726
- He was in the finals.
- Second place? That's losing.

1126
01:18:12,900 --> 01:18:15,232
- Winning is not everything, Glen.
- Right.

1127
01:18:15,402 --> 01:18:16,892
Look at what Cody did...

1128
01:18:17,071 --> 01:18:19,232
Go back to the
"winning isn't everything" thing.

1129
01:18:19,473 --> 01:18:21,737
That doesn't compute, really.

1130
01:18:21,909 --> 01:18:27,404
You know what, Glen? I really hope
someday you can be more like Cody.

1131
01:18:27,881 --> 01:18:29,348
This interview is over.

1132
01:25:00,506 --> 01:25:02,906
Remember when were talking
about you leaving? That was great.

1133
01:25:03,076 --> 01:25:04,703
Remember when
you were gonna go?

1134
01:25:04,878 --> 01:25:06,903
- We were gonna go...
- You should still go.

1135
01:25:07,146 --> 01:25:08,204
It's technical equipment.

1136
01:25:08,381 --> 01:25:12,374
I know what I'm doing. I can unplug
one of your little Hollywood devices.

1137
01:25:12,886 --> 01:25:15,184
The lighting thing,
whatever you call that...

1138
01:25:15,355 --> 01:25:17,220
...and then the microphone thing.

1139
01:25:17,390 --> 01:25:18,721
Go back to Hollywood.

1140
01:25:18,892 --> 01:25:20,382
Cody would never do this.

1141
01:25:21,305 --> 01:25:27,818
